verbose_text: As a key regulator of inflammation [XREF_BIBR], fibrinogen can induce tumor angiogenesis and metastasis by directly interacting with endothelial cells, by indirectly interacting with other regulators of angiogenesis [XREF_BIBR], and by enhancing tumor cell invasion and metastasis through epithelial-to-mesenchymal transition (EMT) signaling [XREF_BIBR].
